00:00:02.604 --> 00:00:03.638 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:11.706 --> 00:01:12.540 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:24.752 --> 00:01:26.854 position:35% line:83% align:start
[narrator]
The Nautilus fell under attack

00:01:26.888 --> 00:01:30.490 position:10% line:83% align:start
by the gigantic new Atlantean
air battleship

00:01:30.525 --> 00:01:32.392 position:13% line:89% align:start
and its advanced weaponry.

00:01:33.561 --> 00:01:37.331 position:10% line:83% align:start
After a valiant fight it was
sunk in the South Pacific.

00:01:37.364 --> 00:01:42.537 position:10% line:83% align:start
Could this be the last voyage
of the uncanny submarine?

00:01:42.570 --> 00:01:43.605 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:01:46.574 --> 00:01:49.677 position:30% line:89% align:start
[alarm beeping]

00:01:50.545 --> 00:01:52.412 position:7% line:89% align:start
[helmsman] Depth is 600 meters.

00:01:52.446 --> 00:01:54.247 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Nemo]
How deep is the Kermodec Trench?

00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:55.883 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
Approximately 10,000 meters.

00:01:55.917 --> 00:01:57.919 position:19% line:83% align:start
We can normally handle
that depth

00:01:57.952 --> 00:01:59.721 position:30% line:83% align:start
with no problem
whatsoever,

00:02:00.855 --> 00:02:01.889 position:27% line:83% align:start
but in the state
that we're in...

00:02:01.923 --> 00:02:03.858 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashing]

00:02:09.429 --> 00:02:11.198 position:33% line:83% align:start
I don't know
how we will stand it.

00:02:11.231 --> 00:02:12.900 position:27% line:83% align:start
The Garfish fleet
is approaching rapidly.

00:02:18.405 --> 00:02:20.407 position:19% line:83% align:start
Depth charges deployed
and approaching.

00:02:20.440 --> 00:02:23.544 position:33% line:89% align:start
[explosions]

00:02:23.578 --> 00:02:26.346 position:30% line:89% align:start
[all screaming]

00:02:31.753 --> 00:02:33.253 position:21% line:89% align:start
[electricity zapping]

00:02:33.286 --> 00:02:34.622 position:33% line:83% align:start
[wireless 1]
Direct hit to port bow!

00:02:34.656 --> 00:02:36.189 position:19% line:83% align:start
[wireless 2] Secondary
living quarters flooding!

00:02:36.223 --> 00:02:38.291 position:27% line:83% align:start
Stern internally
damaged as well!

00:02:38.325 --> 00:02:39.727 position:7% line:89% align:start
Can you tell me where they are?

00:02:40.460 --> 00:02:41.696 position:13% line:89% align:start
[sonar] Directly overhead.

00:02:41.729 --> 00:02:44.297 position:16% line:89% align:start
Distance is 1,800 meters.

00:02:44.331 --> 00:02:45.667 position:41% line:89% align:start
I see.

00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:47.334 position:19% line:89% align:start
Compressed air status?

00:02:47.367 --> 00:02:49.336 position:13% line:83% align:start
[helmsman] Only enough left
for one more surfacing.

00:02:54.441 --> 00:02:57.411 position:16% line:83% align:start
Assemble all crew members
into the central block.

00:02:57.444 --> 00:02:58.946 position:16% line:83% align:start
We'll then strike at them
with our combat blocks,

00:02:58.980 --> 00:03:00.480 position:24% line:89% align:start
last buoyant force.

00:03:00.515 --> 00:03:01.983 position:33% line:89% align:start
But, Captain.

00:03:02.016 --> 00:03:04.886 position:13% line:83% align:start
Otherwise self-destruction
is our only option.

00:03:04.919 --> 00:03:07.320 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Now, First Officer.
-Aye.

00:03:07.354 --> 00:03:10.290 position:35% line:83% align:start
All hands,
report to the secondary shelter

00:03:10.323 --> 00:03:11.959 position:21% line:89% align:start
in the central block.

00:03:11.993 --> 00:03:14.796 position:27% line:83% align:start
Repeat, all hands
report to the secondary shelter

00:03:14.829 --> 00:03:16.531 position:21% line:89% align:start
in the central block.

00:03:16.564 --> 00:03:19.366 position:21% line:83% align:start
We will be separating
from the combat block.

00:03:19.399 --> 00:03:20.935 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Separating?
-What's that?

00:03:20.968 --> 00:03:22.235 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:03:22.269 --> 00:03:23.303 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Electra]
Can you hear me, Jean?

00:03:23.336 --> 00:03:24.271 position:35% line:89% align:start
Yes, I can.

00:03:24.939 --> 00:03:26.574 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'm so sorry for before.

00:03:27.875 --> 00:03:29.544 position:33% line:83% align:start
You are safe
right where you are.

00:03:29.577 --> 00:03:30.745 position:33% line:89% align:start
Do not move.

00:03:31.411 --> 00:03:32.914 position:33% line:89% align:start
Ms. Electra!

00:03:32.947 --> 00:03:35.750 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're going to be fine,
so please don't worry.

00:03:35.783 --> 00:03:38.653 position:35% line:89% align:start
Uh... wait!

00:03:38.686 --> 00:03:39.821 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'll see you later.

00:03:48.295 --> 00:03:49.897 position:16% line:83% align:start
Central block separation
is complete.

00:03:49.931 --> 00:03:52.365 position:5% line:89% align:start
Power sources are switched over.

00:03:52.399 --> 00:03:53.868 position:19% line:83% align:start
[crew] Combat block is
functioning

00:03:53.901 --> 00:03:55.636 position:16% line:89% align:start
independent of main unit.

00:03:55.670 --> 00:03:57.805 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Electra] Detonation
is set for 800 meters,

00:03:57.839 --> 00:04:00.373 position:7% line:89% align:start
distance to fleet 1,500 meters.

00:04:00.407 --> 00:04:01.909 position:10% line:89% align:start
Release the combat block now.

00:04:01.943 --> 00:04:02.944 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Electra] Aye.

00:04:04.712 --> 00:04:05.847 position:41% line:89% align:start
[beeps]

00:04:19.660 --> 00:04:20.962 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:04:29.604 --> 00:04:31.572 position:24% line:83% align:start
[operator] Nautilus
has separated into two parts

00:04:31.606 --> 00:04:34.307 position:13% line:89% align:start
at a depth of 2,400 meters.

00:04:34.341 --> 00:04:35.910 position:35% line:89% align:start
We did it.

00:04:35.943 --> 00:04:37.678 position:24% line:83% align:start
The water pressure
has torn them asunder!

00:04:37.712 --> 00:04:39.046 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Gargoyle] Incorrect.

00:04:39.947 --> 00:04:42.950 position:19% line:83% align:start
They've only amputated
the weakest link.

00:04:42.984 --> 00:04:44.786 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's... that's impossible.

00:04:44.819 --> 00:04:47.354 position:27% line:83% align:start
Tell the Garfish
to retreat immediately

00:04:47.387 --> 00:04:49.056 position:10% line:89% align:start
or they will soon regret it.

00:04:49.657 --> 00:04:50.658 position:35% line:89% align:start
Understood.

00:04:51.759 --> 00:04:53.393 position:35% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:05:01.736 --> 00:05:04.371 position:13% line:83% align:start
[sonar] Garfish destroyed,
shock wave approaching.

00:05:04.404 --> 00:05:06.306 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[explosion]
-[rumbling]

00:05:10.377 --> 00:05:12.647 position:33% line:83% align:start
That's always
such a terrible sound.

00:05:13.614 --> 00:05:15.049 position:7% line:89% align:start
It could happen to us as well.

00:05:15.082 --> 00:05:16.918 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

00:05:16.951 --> 00:05:18.920 position:7% line:83% align:start
It is worth noting that we have
no power left to surface, sir.

00:05:23.524 --> 00:05:26.060 position:35% line:83% align:start
[operator]
The Garfish fleet is destroyed.

00:05:26.093 --> 00:05:28.729 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm terribly sorry,
Lord Gargoyle.

00:05:28.763 --> 00:05:29.831 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Gargoyle] Damn them.

00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:33.000 position:16% line:83% align:start
How severe is the damage
to the Nautilus?

00:05:33.034 --> 00:05:34.836 position:27% line:83% align:start
Sir, that is not
fully known yet.

00:05:35.903 --> 00:05:37.404 position:33% line:89% align:start
So resilient.

00:05:44.411 --> 00:05:45.847 position:35% line:89% align:start
[all gasps]

00:05:45.880 --> 00:05:48.115 position:19% line:83% align:start
-What on earth is that?
-Good question.

00:05:51.118 --> 00:05:52.753 position:7% line:89% align:start
It is a deep sea current, sir.

00:05:52.787 --> 00:05:54.555 position:19% line:83% align:start
It is flowing southwest
at six knots.

00:05:56.057 --> 00:05:57.124 position:33% line:89% align:start
I understand.

00:05:58.159 --> 00:05:59.459 position:21% line:89% align:start
Will you see to this?

00:06:00.862 --> 00:06:01.896 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Electra] Aye.

00:06:10.738 --> 00:06:13.674 position:13% line:83% align:start
[operator] The Nautilus has
reached a depth of 4,000 meters.

00:06:14.508 --> 00:06:16.844 position:35% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry,
but it's beyond our range.

00:06:17.745 --> 00:06:19.680 position:7% line:83% align:start
[follower 1] It couldn't stand
another assault

00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:23.050 position:16% line:83% align:start
even if its hull was made
from a space titanium alloy.

00:06:23.084 --> 00:06:25.686 position:33% line:83% align:start
[follower 2]
Their damage is quite extensive.

00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:28.155 position:5% line:83% align:start
[follower 3] It would be a short
exercise to finish them off.

00:06:28.189 --> 00:06:31.092 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Gargoyle] We cornered
it but couldn't kill it.

00:06:31.125 --> 00:06:33.160 position:10% line:89% align:start
Who is responsible for this?

00:06:33.194 --> 00:06:34.896 position:33% line:89% align:start
[both gasps]

00:06:34.929 --> 00:06:36.998 position:19% line:83% align:start
[follower 1] The fault
is entirely mine, my Lord.

00:06:37.031 --> 00:06:38.498 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Gargoyle] Pay no mind.

00:06:39.667 --> 00:06:43.137 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's a pity we couldn't witness
the end of the Nautilus.

00:06:44.906 --> 00:06:46.741 position:13% line:89% align:start
Report this to the Emperor.

00:06:46.774 --> 00:06:47.875 position:19% line:89% align:start
[followers] Understood.

00:06:51.579 --> 00:06:52.713 position:24% line:89% align:start
[man] Emperor Neo,

00:06:56.183 --> 00:06:58.853 position:7% line:89% align:start
we have a report from Gargoyle.

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:00.888 position:21% line:89% align:start
Put it through, now.

00:07:00.922 --> 00:07:03.024 position:16% line:89% align:start
[man] Your will is done.

00:07:03.057 --> 00:07:05.092 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Gargoyle] Good
news, Emperor Neo.

00:07:05.126 --> 00:07:08.529 position:16% line:83% align:start
The Nautilus lies ruined
at a depth of 4,000 meters

00:07:08.562 --> 00:07:10.064 position:19% line:89% align:start
in the Kermodec Trench.

00:07:10.097 --> 00:07:12.465 position:19% line:89% align:start
All are believed dead.

00:07:12.499 --> 00:07:13.834 position:30% line:89% align:start
Pleasant news.

00:07:13.868 --> 00:07:15.803 position:10% line:89% align:start
You have served me very well.

00:07:15.836 --> 00:07:17.538 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Gargoyle] Excellency,

00:07:17.571 --> 00:07:19.907 position:30% line:83% align:start
may I impose on
Your Highness' goodwill

00:07:19.941 --> 00:07:22.944 position:13% line:83% align:start
and request your assistance
in locating Nemo

00:07:22.977 --> 00:07:24.979 position:19% line:89% align:start
and Nadia's Blue Water?

00:07:25.746 --> 00:07:27.214 position:30% line:89% align:start
It is granted.

00:07:27.248 --> 00:07:29.482 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Gargoyle] Excellency,
we are most grateful.

00:07:29.517 --> 00:07:31.552 position:24% line:83% align:start
I will present you
with a detailed report

00:07:31.585 --> 00:07:33.688 position:19% line:83% align:start
in the fullness of time
upon my return.

00:07:33.721 --> 00:07:35.156 position:16% line:89% align:start
I long to see you again.

00:07:36.757 --> 00:07:38.059 position:33% line:89% align:start
I shall wait.

00:07:38.092 --> 00:07:41.762 position:35% line:83% align:start
Excellency,
I remain your humble servant.

00:07:45.132 --> 00:07:47.635 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Neo] Nemo and Nadia
have been killed.

00:07:48.736 --> 00:07:51.072 position:19% line:89% align:start
For over 12,000 years,

00:07:51.105 --> 00:07:53.874 position:33% line:83% align:start
so much blood
has been sacrificed

00:07:53.908 --> 00:07:55.609 position:19% line:89% align:start
all for the Blue Water.

00:08:05.820 --> 00:08:07.788 position:24% line:83% align:start
Command crew report
to the subordinate bridge.

00:08:09.123 --> 00:08:11.592 position:5% line:83% align:start
-I will instruct you there.
-[Electra] Aye, sir.

00:08:11.625 --> 00:08:12.994 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Marie laughing]

00:08:21.802 --> 00:08:22.870 position:38% line:89% align:start
[shrieks]

00:08:24.905 --> 00:08:25.740 position:33% line:89% align:start
Come with me.

00:08:25.773 --> 00:08:27.208 position:41% line:89% align:start
[purrs]

00:08:28.142 --> 00:08:29.944 position:16% line:89% align:start
Where are we going, huh?

00:08:31.912 --> 00:08:32.913 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia?

00:08:33.581 --> 00:08:34.815 position:27% line:89% align:start
Tell me, Nadia.

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:40.154 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:08:41.188 --> 00:08:42.523 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow.

00:08:42.790 --> 00:08:43.824 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Jean] Is this...

00:08:43.858 --> 00:08:44.992 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Nadia]
These are your quarters?

00:08:45.026 --> 00:08:46.560 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yes, that's correct.

00:08:47.795 --> 00:08:49.997 position:13% line:83% align:start
But I thought that you said
no one else was allowed in here.

00:08:50.031 --> 00:08:52.633 position:19% line:83% align:start
This will be jettisoned
from the main block, Jean.

00:08:53.768 --> 00:08:54.802 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:08:55.903 --> 00:08:57.838 position:16% line:83% align:start
It is best for all of us
if you would leave the ship.

00:08:58.172 --> 00:08:59.607 position:38% line:89% align:start
But why?

00:08:59.640 --> 00:09:01.742 position:27% line:83% align:start
Without advanced
technological knowledge

00:09:01.776 --> 00:09:04.311 position:21% line:83% align:start
you are useless here,
do you understand that?

00:09:04.345 --> 00:09:08.215 position:13% line:83% align:start
Captain, I will do anything
to help, anything at all, sir.

00:09:17.858 --> 00:09:21.262 position:24% line:83% align:start
Now, Listen, Jean,
please look after Nadia for me.

00:09:25.633 --> 00:09:27.835 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, I...

00:09:30.971 --> 00:09:32.206 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:09:35.810 --> 00:09:37.812 position:10% line:89% align:start
Me too, Captain Nemo, me too.

00:09:37.845 --> 00:09:40.648 position:7% line:83% align:start
You can hug me if you want to,
Captain Nemo.

00:09:40.681 --> 00:09:41.816 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hug me.

00:09:41.849 --> 00:09:43.084 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hug me!

00:09:43.117 --> 00:09:44.652 position:35% line:83% align:start
-All right.
-Wee!

00:09:44.685 --> 00:09:47.154 position:16% line:83% align:start
Aren't you afraid of me,
my dear Marie?

00:09:47.188 --> 00:09:51.258 position:13% line:83% align:start
I guess, just a little bit,
but I also love you too, okay?

00:09:51.292 --> 00:09:52.927 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[giggles]
-[Nemo chuckling]

00:09:57.898 --> 00:10:00.768 position:7% line:89% align:start
Jean, take care of her as well.

00:10:01.902 --> 00:10:03.838 position:44% line:89% align:start
Bye.

00:10:03.871 --> 00:10:04.905 position:35% line:89% align:start
[giggling]

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:07.274 position:38% line:89% align:start
Captain!

00:10:14.915 --> 00:10:15.550 position:41% line:89% align:start
[thuds]

00:10:19.420 --> 00:10:20.254 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:10:30.131 --> 00:10:31.098 position:19% line:89% align:start
Why are you still here?

00:10:35.302 --> 00:10:39.306 position:16% line:89% align:start
â™ª The Secret Blue Water

00:10:40.074 --> 00:10:41.308 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:10:44.378 --> 00:10:45.412 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-Jean?

00:10:45.446 --> 00:10:47.148 position:19% line:89% align:start
Who's firing a pistol?

00:10:48.883 --> 00:10:51.051 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[grunts]
-[metal banging]

00:10:51.986 --> 00:10:53.053 position:19% line:89% align:start
It won't open. Help me.

00:10:53.087 --> 00:10:54.421 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm trying. Hold on.

00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:57.291 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-[Electra] My life ended

00:10:57.324 --> 00:11:01.028 position:13% line:83% align:start
13 years ago when I left my
name and my land.

00:11:01.829 --> 00:11:03.764 position:21% line:83% align:start
The day you destroyed
my homeland

00:11:03.797 --> 00:11:05.799 position:10% line:89% align:start
and my family along with it,

00:11:05.833 --> 00:11:07.401 position:7% line:89% align:start
the day of that blinding light

00:11:07.434 --> 00:11:10.204 position:7% line:83% align:start
was the beginning of everything
wasn't it, dear Captain?

00:11:10.237 --> 00:11:11.272 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:13.674 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:11:14.341 --> 00:11:17.311 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:11:42.403 --> 00:11:45.005 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Electra] That light killed
the Queen of Tartessos,

00:11:45.940 --> 00:11:46.774 position:35% line:89% align:start
your wife.

00:11:48.409 --> 00:11:50.778 position:30% line:83% align:start
We had no idea
what was to follow,

00:11:51.812 --> 00:11:54.381 position:16% line:83% align:start
a coup d'etat that began
with assassination

00:11:56.417 --> 00:11:59.820 position:19% line:83% align:start
and ended with victory
for the filthy rebels.

00:12:02.557 --> 00:12:05.459 position:27% line:83% align:start
But the bloodshed
had only begun.

00:12:05.492 --> 00:12:06.460 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:12:15.302 --> 00:12:16.870 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Electra] The leader
of the rebels was the man

00:12:16.904 --> 00:12:19.139 position:10% line:89% align:start
who called himself Gargoyle.

00:12:20.040 --> 00:12:23.143 position:19% line:83% align:start
He changed the name of
our kingdom from Tartessos

00:12:23.177 --> 00:12:24.211 position:27% line:89% align:start
to Neo Atlantis.

00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:35.956 position:38% line:83% align:start
All with
the support of Emperor Neo

00:12:35.990 --> 00:12:39.393 position:5% line:83% align:start
who wanted to unlock the ancient
secret of the Tower of Babel.

00:12:42.329 --> 00:12:43.998 position:19% line:89% align:start
The seals were broken.

00:12:48.068 --> 00:12:51.038 position:24% line:83% align:start
The Tower of Babel
regained its natural power.

00:12:51.071 --> 00:12:53.841 position:19% line:83% align:start
When Gargoyle attempted
to demonstrate

00:12:53.874 --> 00:12:55.409 position:7% line:89% align:start
the tower's destructive power,

00:12:55.442 --> 00:12:58.145 position:16% line:89% align:start
our tragedy really began.

00:12:58.178 --> 00:12:59.413 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:12:59.446 --> 00:13:01.415 position:10% line:89% align:start
Lightning overtook the land.

00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:02.416 position:27% line:89% align:start
[glass breaking]

00:13:04.385 --> 00:13:07.187 position:35% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:13:11.593 --> 00:13:13.827 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Electra] Fire and wind raged

00:13:13.861 --> 00:13:16.330 position:19% line:83% align:start
throughout the kingdom
for seven days.

00:13:16.363 --> 00:13:17.931 position:21% line:89% align:start
It was a sea of fire.

00:13:19.567 --> 00:13:23.103 position:16% line:83% align:start
The angry water and earth
swallowed everything,

00:13:23.137 --> 00:13:26.073 position:27% line:83% align:start
as if to blot out
this abomination,

00:13:26.106 --> 00:13:28.510 position:30% line:83% align:start
as if to cover
the gates of hell.

00:13:31.445 --> 00:13:33.380 position:24% line:89% align:start
The city was lost.

00:14:04.311 --> 00:14:06.347 position:21% line:89% align:start
Everything was gone.

00:14:15.623 --> 00:14:18.526 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:14:21.596 --> 00:14:24.632 position:30% line:89% align:start
[crows cawing]

00:14:57.364 --> 00:15:00.401 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Electra crying]

00:15:14.281 --> 00:15:16.216 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:15:27.461 --> 00:15:29.229 position:21% line:89% align:start
My brother was dead.

00:15:38.673 --> 00:15:41.676 position:7% line:83% align:start
I slept two nights before I saw
another living soul.

00:15:44.779 --> 00:15:46.413 position:35% line:89% align:start
It was you.

00:15:46.447 --> 00:15:48.148 position:30% line:89% align:start
[wind howling]

00:16:00.528 --> 00:16:03.464 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:16:10.170 --> 00:16:12.372 position:27% line:89% align:start
[birds chirping]

00:16:16.310 --> 00:16:19.581 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Electra] I was very grateful
to the man who saved me.

00:16:21.683 --> 00:16:24.151 position:5% line:89% align:start
And when I realized it was love,

00:16:25.452 --> 00:16:26.721 position:30% line:89% align:start
I was so happy.

00:16:28.590 --> 00:16:29.757 position:30% line:89% align:start
I was content.

00:16:34.428 --> 00:16:38.733 position:13% line:83% align:start
But then I learned exactly
what I never wanted to know.

00:16:46.139 --> 00:16:48.308 position:30% line:83% align:start
[engineer] Are
you really going to raise her?

00:16:48.342 --> 00:16:51.378 position:27% line:83% align:start
We live in a hell
that she should have no part of.

00:16:51.411 --> 00:16:54.314 position:7% line:83% align:start
She has suffered enough without
the added burden of our mission.

00:16:54.348 --> 00:16:57.117 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Nemo] I've been prepared
for this for five years now.

00:16:57.150 --> 00:16:59.721 position:19% line:83% align:start
We must fight Gargoyle
to the bloody end.

00:16:59.754 --> 00:17:01.689 position:21% line:83% align:start
Helping her would be
a small victory

00:17:01.723 --> 00:17:03.357 position:7% line:89% align:start
at the start of a long battle.

00:17:03.390 --> 00:17:05.092 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
You want to raise her to atone

00:17:05.125 --> 00:17:07.027 position:38% line:83% align:start
for what
happened five years ago?

00:17:08.796 --> 00:17:11.198 position:30% line:83% align:start
You were right
to do what you did.

00:17:11.799 --> 00:17:14.334 position:16% line:83% align:start
You were right to destroy
the Tower of Babel

00:17:14.368 --> 00:17:16.169 position:21% line:89% align:start
with your own hands.

00:17:16.203 --> 00:17:18.673 position:24% line:83% align:start
[man] He's correct.
There was no other way.

00:17:18.706 --> 00:17:22.175 position:7% line:83% align:start
You had to pull the Blue Water
out of the control device.

00:17:22.209 --> 00:17:24.411 position:13% line:83% align:start
You had to cause the tower
to self-destruct.

00:17:24.879 --> 00:17:26.681 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
You want her as a substitute

00:17:26.714 --> 00:17:28.348 position:19% line:89% align:start
for your dead daughter.

00:17:28.382 --> 00:17:30.552 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Nemo] Nothing could be further
from the truth.

00:17:33.521 --> 00:17:38.492 position:7% line:83% align:start
She has seized her own survival
under the very jaws of Hell.

00:17:39.794 --> 00:17:43.665 position:19% line:83% align:start
I only want to help her
grasp the life she desires

00:17:43.698 --> 00:17:45.633 position:24% line:89% align:start
anyway that I can.

00:17:46.266 --> 00:17:47.869 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
You allow her to come with us

00:17:47.902 --> 00:17:50.170 position:13% line:89% align:start
if that's what she desires?

00:17:50.203 --> 00:17:53.173 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Nemo] I will do what I must
to return the balance

00:17:53.206 --> 00:17:55.643 position:27% line:83% align:start
that has been so
savagely disturbed.

00:17:55.677 --> 00:17:57.779 position:30% line:83% align:start
[engineer] And
you will bring her into a world

00:17:57.812 --> 00:18:00.280 position:13% line:83% align:start
where all our lives will be
in constant danger?

00:18:00.314 --> 00:18:03.417 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Nemo] There are as many lives
as there are men.

00:18:03.450 --> 00:18:06.688 position:5% line:83% align:start
[engineer] Well, man cannot live
on hatred alone.

00:18:08.188 --> 00:18:10.525 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Electra] Oh, how I hated you,

00:18:10.558 --> 00:18:13.160 position:16% line:89% align:start
how I wanted to kill you.

00:18:13.193 --> 00:18:15.830 position:16% line:83% align:start
I understand that you had
to destroy the tower.

00:18:15.863 --> 00:18:18.365 position:19% line:83% align:start
If you hadn't, Gargoyle
would've devastated the world

00:18:18.398 --> 00:18:19.667 position:33% line:89% align:start
13 years ago.

00:18:20.535 --> 00:18:24.404 position:7% line:89% align:start
But my father, mother, brother,

00:18:24.438 --> 00:18:26.273 position:21% line:83% align:start
and all of the people
who were killed

00:18:26.306 --> 00:18:29.242 position:30% line:83% align:start
must be asking
a very familiar question.

00:18:31.278 --> 00:18:33.715 position:19% line:83% align:start
How can a man like you
continue to live?

00:18:33.748 --> 00:18:37.552 position:13% line:83% align:start
I believed you intended to
kill Gargoyle and Emperor Neo,

00:18:37.585 --> 00:18:39.486 position:16% line:89% align:start
and destroy Neo Atlantis.

00:18:40.588 --> 00:18:43.725 position:5% line:83% align:start
I believed that you would expend
as much blood as needed

00:18:43.758 --> 00:18:45.627 position:13% line:89% align:start
to accomplish that mission.

00:18:45.660 --> 00:18:48.261 position:27% line:83% align:start
That's the reason
I followed you all these years.

00:18:48.730 --> 00:18:51.465 position:5% line:89% align:start
I believed you and I adored you.

00:18:52.332 --> 00:18:54.368 position:24% line:83% align:start
I didn't care that
I was just a substitute

00:18:54.401 --> 00:18:56.571 position:27% line:83% align:start
for the daughter
you loved and lost.

00:18:56.604 --> 00:18:58.740 position:33% line:83% align:start
I just wanted
to be by your side.

00:19:02.777 --> 00:19:05.613 position:21% line:83% align:start
That is until the day
your real daughter appeared

00:19:05.647 --> 00:19:07.447 position:7% line:89% align:start
before you with her Blue Water.

00:19:08.348 --> 00:19:10.417 position:21% line:89% align:start
I feared her so much.

00:19:10.450 --> 00:19:12.219 position:24% line:83% align:start
I knew beyond doubt
that she would steal your heart

00:19:12.252 --> 00:19:13.286 position:33% line:89% align:start
away from me,

00:19:14.488 --> 00:19:16.858 position:19% line:83% align:start
but you didn't tell her
that you were her father.

00:19:16.891 --> 00:19:18.793 position:16% line:83% align:start
You stoked the vengeance
in your heart

00:19:18.826 --> 00:19:20.895 position:13% line:89% align:start
against the Neo Atlanteans.

00:19:20.928 --> 00:19:23.598 position:10% line:89% align:start
You remained the man I loved.

00:19:23.631 --> 00:19:24.799 position:30% line:89% align:start
So tell me why.

00:19:25.667 --> 00:19:26.534 position:27% line:89% align:start
Can you tell me?

00:19:27.602 --> 00:19:30.672 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why did you go back
to being an ordinary father?

00:19:31.539 --> 00:19:34.474 position:19% line:83% align:start
Why couldn't you remain
the man I fell in love with?

00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:39.781 position:33% line:89% align:start
Goodbye, sir.

00:19:41.348 --> 00:19:42.784 position:19% line:89% align:start
No, please don't do it!

00:19:42.817 --> 00:19:44.619 position:27% line:89% align:start
Don't shoot him!

00:19:45.953 --> 00:19:46.621 position:30% line:89% align:start
Let her do it!

00:19:48.656 --> 00:19:50.725 position:10% line:89% align:start
I knew all about your hatred.

00:19:50.758 --> 00:19:51.926 position:19% line:89% align:start
You may do as you wish.

00:19:51.959 --> 00:19:52.794 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sir!

00:19:53.928 --> 00:19:55.395 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunshots]

00:20:03.403 --> 00:20:06.239 position:5% line:83% align:start
One shot is enough to kill a man
such as yourself.

00:20:08.375 --> 00:20:09.577 position:41% line:89% align:start
It is.

00:20:12.647 --> 00:20:14.582 position:21% line:89% align:start
I want you to tell me

00:20:14.615 --> 00:20:17.350 position:7% line:83% align:start
why you couldn't kill yourself
to destroy Gargoyle?

00:20:19.587 --> 00:20:22.590 position:19% line:83% align:start
I couldn't allow myself
to make the same mistake.

00:20:22.623 --> 00:20:24.257 position:38% line:89% align:start
Mistake?

00:20:24.759 --> 00:20:27.929 position:13% line:83% align:start
The mistake that caused you
to destroy your homeland

00:20:27.962 --> 00:20:30.330 position:21% line:83% align:start
and kill every person
you ever loved?

00:20:31.398 --> 00:20:32.232 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:20:34.836 --> 00:20:36.804 position:10% line:89% align:start
I must atone for what I did.

00:20:37.772 --> 00:20:39.507 position:35% line:89% align:start
That's all.

00:20:39.540 --> 00:20:41.943 position:10% line:89% align:start
I live only for that purpose.

00:20:41.976 --> 00:20:43.745 position:13% line:83% align:start
Then why didn't you destroy
yourself

00:20:43.778 --> 00:20:46.581 position:21% line:83% align:start
when you finally had
the chance?

00:20:46.614 --> 00:20:48.850 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Answer.
-For 13 years,

00:20:50.518 --> 00:20:51.919 position:19% line:89% align:start
you've been by my side.

00:20:52.687 --> 00:20:55.355 position:27% line:83% align:start
I think of you as
my own daughter.

00:20:55.388 --> 00:20:57.357 position:13% line:83% align:start
I could not do that to you,
my child.

00:21:00.928 --> 00:21:03.898 position:13% line:89% align:start
Electra, I did it for you.

00:21:11.739 --> 00:21:13.040 position:30% line:89% align:start
You are unfair.

00:21:13.074 --> 00:21:14.709 position:21% line:89% align:start
I can't kill you now.

00:21:19.647 --> 00:21:22.282 position:13% line:83% align:start
You dare tell me something
like this at this moment

00:21:25.052 --> 00:21:27.755 position:27% line:83% align:start
and so I will use
this last bullet on myself.

00:21:27.789 --> 00:21:30.423 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll give you back
the life you gave me.

00:21:30.457 --> 00:21:31.626 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:21:37.665 --> 00:21:40.300 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Electra cries]

00:21:41.434 --> 00:21:43.370 position:35% line:83% align:start
Don't be so
careless with your life!

00:21:43.403 --> 00:21:45.840 position:19% line:83% align:start
Electra, you must live
to do what you must do!

00:21:45.873 --> 00:21:48.943 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sobbing]

00:21:53.748 --> 00:21:56.050 position:35% line:83% align:start
[engineer]
Man cannot live on hatred alone.

00:21:58.485 --> 00:22:00.487 position:7% line:89% align:start
That's true, isn't it, Captain?

00:22:02.957 --> 00:22:05.893 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:22:05.927 --> 00:22:08.696 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:22:18.072 --> 00:22:19.106 position:33% line:89% align:start
Live, Nadia!

00:22:19.140 --> 00:22:20.541 position:44% line:89% align:start
Live!

00:22:20.575 --> 00:22:22.844 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:22:55.610 --> 00:22:56.911 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia?

00:22:56.944 --> 00:22:58.880 position:30% line:89% align:start
[King purring]

00:22:59.614 --> 00:23:00.748 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:23:02.683 --> 00:23:03.684 position:44% line:89% align:start
King!

00:23:03.718 --> 00:23:05.052 position:35% line:89% align:start
Stop that!

00:23:06.153 --> 00:23:09.891 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:23:24.538 --> 00:23:25.740 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Father.

00:23:26.741 --> 00:23:28.576 position:41% line:89% align:start
[cries]

00:23:33.214 --> 00:23:34.048 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia.

00:23:35.016 --> 00:23:37.952 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:23:55.937 --> 00:23:56.771 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

